`crates/ctx-summarize` is the `ctx-summarize` binary crate as a whole: a repo-scoped summarizer that generates leaf `.ctx` files via an LLM agent and rolls them up bottom-up into `rollup.ctx`, plus its integration test suite.

`src/` holds all logic: strict layering (main.rs → cli.rs → runner.rs), the `Fs`/`Agent` trait seams, `cpath.rs` path handling, and the shared `SummError` type. The two load-bearing cross-cutting contracts are the `--- label ---` rollup input format and the `.context` mirror-path duplication with `ctx-context` — both must be checked wherever they're touched. Prompts live in files, never as code constants; `intent.md` is read-only to this crate. Rollup ordering (leaf-to-root, strictly-decreasing depth) is guaranteed by `runner::affected_dirs`.

`tests/` is a single integration file (`summarize.rs`) exercising this ordering guarantee, gating errors (path traversal, missing prompts, oversized scope, secret-like paths), and the Fs/Agent contracts via fakes and real subprocess calls. Its `FakeFs`/`RecordingAgent` doubles must track any trait signature change in `src/fs.rs` / `src/agent.rs` — this is the one coupling that spans the two subdirectories: a trait change in `src/` breaks compilation in `tests/` until the doubles are updated.

No divergence from stated intent at this level (no `intent.md` present here).